<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 11:27PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Towns
County through 1145 PM EDT...
At 1127 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Titus, or 7 miles
east of Hiawassee, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Tate City, Titus and Plum Orchard Gap Shelter.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
